{{NHL award
|trophy_name = Maurice "Rocket" Richard Trophy
|Image = Hhof maurice richard.jpg
|Established= [[1998-99 NHL season]]
|Holder = [[Vincent Lecavalier]]
|Awarded = [[National Hockey League]]'s top goal scorer
}} 
The '''Maurice "Rocket" Richard Trophy''', also known as the '''Maurice Richard Trophy'''<ref name="Richard history">{{cite web|url=http://www.nhl.com/trophies/richard.html|title=Maurice "Rocket" Richard Trophy history|accessdate=2007-08-21|publisher=NHL.com}}</ref> is awarded annually to the leading goal scorer in the [[National Hockey League]]. It was donated to the [[NHL]] by the [[Montreal Canadiens]] hockey club in [[1998-99 NHL season|1998-99]] and is named in honour of the legendary Montreal Canadiens [[Winger (ice hockey)|right winger]] [[Maurice Richard|Maurice "Rocket" Richard]]. The Trophy has been awarded at the end of eight seasons to eight different players. The current holder is [[Vincent Lecavalier]] of the [[Tampa Bay Lightning]], who scored 52 goals during the [[2006-07 NHL season|2006-07 season]] to earn his first Richard Trophy. This list contains the winners of the official trophy, as well as the goal scoring leaders prior to the trophy's inception.

==History==
[[Image:Maurice richard profile.jpg|left|100px|thumb|[[Maurice Richard]], the namesake for the trophy.]]
The Maurice "Rocket" Richard Trophy was donated by the Montreal Canadiens in 1999, and was first awarded at the end of the 1998-99 season. It is the newest of the NHL's trophies and is named in honour of the legendary [[Winger (ice hockey)|right winger]] [[Maurice Richard|Maurice "Rocket" Richard]], who spent his eighteen-season career with the Canadiens. He led the NHL in goal scoring five times, and in [[1944-45 NHL season|1944-45]] he became the first player in NHL history to score [[50 goals in 50 games|50 goals]] in one season.<ref name="Richard history2">{{cite web|url=http://www.legendsofhockey.net/html/silver_splashrocketrichard.htm|title=Maurice "Rocket" Richard Trophy history|accessdate=2007-07-31|publisher=Legendsofhockey.net}}</ref>

[[Pavel Bure]] and [[Jarome Iginla]] are the only players to have won the trophy twice. The [[2003-04 NHL season|2003-04 season]] featured a three-way tie between Iginla, [[Ilya Kovalchuk]] and [[Rick Nash]], the only tie in the short history of the trophy.

Although the winner of the [[Art Ross Trophy|NHL's leading points scorer]] often wins the [[Hart Memorial Trophy]] as league MVP, no winner of the Maurice "Rocket" Richard Trophy has won the Hart Trophy for the same season.<ref name="Hart history">{{cite web|url=http://www.nhl.com/trophies/hart.html|title=Hart Memorial Trophy history|accessdate=2007-08-22|publisher=NHL.com}}</ref>
{{clear}}

